(13912, 1, '2020-08-05 05:19:19', '2020-08-05 05:19:19', '[vc_row][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"United Kingdom Education\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]United Kingdom holds Education as one of the pillars of the society and its education system is among the oldest in the world. Most degree programs in the UK are of three years, and a masters program is typically between one and two years. Also, the IELTS test bar for UK student visa is lower compared to other countries. An international student in the UK is typically allowed to work up to 20 hours a week during school term, and up to full-time when school is out of term.\n\n[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Why Choose United Kingdom for Education.\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]<strong>Study at the best and most prestigious universities in the world</strong>\nThe United Kingdom boasts of some of the most prestigious and historical university campuses in the world. Studying at these campuses will enable you to harness the foundations of a rich and varied educational system that dates back several centuries\n\n<strong>A degree from the United Kingdom adds on a lot of weight to ones resume</strong>\nThe United Kingdom educational system with its focus on research and practical know how, has earned itself a reputation for graduate employability. When youstudy in UK,your educational qualifications are recognized all over the world and help you in your career.\n\n<strong>One can work while studying in UK</strong>\nThe United Kingdom allows students to work while you study for an undergraduate or post graduate course in the country. You can work for up to 20 hours a week when the academic session is in progress\n\n<strong>Excellent research facilities for students</strong>\nThe United Kingdom is one of the best countries for research infrastructure as well as research output. A number of award winning research projects have emerged from universities in the UK. As a student pursuing research you will have significant advantage when you study in UK\n\n<strong>Dual degree programs</strong>\nThe United Kingdom allows students to study in joint dual degree programs. The advantage of a dual degree program is that it allows you to explore two subjects in one degree program. For example students could take up a dual degree in product engineering and financial management or art history and architecture[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Scholarships for Study in United Kingdom.\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]There are many scholarship programs which students can pursue who are planning to study in United Kingdom, but cannot able to afford the fees. The scholarships typically cover either the entire or part of the costs of tuition in UK. Here are some of the most coveted<strong><a href=\"https://study-uk.britishcouncil.org/options/scholarships-financial-support\">scholarships for studying in United Kingdom</a></strong>[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=\"0px\" disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"13721\" img_size=\"530*300\" el_class=\"ts-border-radius-1\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][themestek-list icon_type=\"themestek_liviza_business_icon\" icon_icon_themestek_liviza_business_icon=\"themestek-liviza-business-icon themestek-liviza-business-icon-check\" line1=\"R28lMjB0byUyMHRoZSUyMG9mZmljaWFsJTIwd2Vic2l0ZSUyMElFTFRTJTIwYW5kJTIwY3JlYXRlJTIwcHJvZmlsZS4=\" line2=\"Q2hlY2slMjBJbmZvcm1hdGlvbiUyMHByb3ZpZGUlMjBpbiUyMHlvdXIlMjBwYXNzcG9ydC4=\" line3=\"U3BlYWtpbmclMjBvciUyMHdyaXRpbmclMjBzY29yZSUyMHJldmlldyUyMGZvcm0lMjB5b3VyJTIwZXhhbS4=\" line4=\"QWRkaXRpb25hbCUyMHJlcG9ydHMlMjBpbnN0aXR1dGlvbiUyMG9mJTIwY29hY2hpbmclMjBjZW50ZXI=\" line5=\"TmVlZCUyMGV4cGVydGlzZSUyMGhlbHAlMkMlMjB3aGVyZXZlciUyMHlvdSUyMGluJTIwdGhlJTIwd29ybGQu\" css=\".vc_custom_1580792535630{padding-bottom: 20px !important;}\" el_class=\"themestek-lis