(13916, 1, '2020-08-05 05:20:23', '2020-08-05 05:20:23', '[vc_row][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Australia Education\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]Australia is currently the third most popular destination for international students in the English-speaking world (after US, UK). Graduates from Australian schools are highly sought after due to the impressive international reputation of the Australian education system. Do you know that eight of the top 100 universities in the world are in Australia and the country is ranked 9ththin the world by University system ranking! Living expenses and tuition costs are considerably lower here than they are in US and UK. International students who are perusing their studies in Australia can work up to 40 hours per fortnight, allowing them to earn money, gain useful work experience and exposure in a developed country and meet a variety of new people. Both IELTS and PTE are considered for student visa applicants and later for PR.[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Why Choose Australia for Education\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]<strong>Academic Excellence:</strong><b>\n</b>Australia has some of the highest number of universities that are ranked among the top 100 in the world. Australian universities have earned a worldwide reputation for their expert faculty, academic rigor of the subjects as well as research facilities. Some of the best research in the world emanates from universities in Australia.\n\n<strong>All courses are taught in English:</strong><b>\n</b>One advantage for students, who go to study abroad education in Australia, is that the courses are taught in English and the language of communication in and around the campus will be English.\n\n<strong>Students can bring their spouse/dependents along while studying in Australian Universities:</strong><b>\n</b>One of the major pulls of studying in Australia is that it has the unique benefit of allowing spouses to accompany students while they pursue a course in the country. In certain cases even parents can accompany the student in the role of guardians.\n\n<strong>Work while you study in Australia:</strong><b>\n</b>Australia allows international students to take up some occupation on a part time basis while they are pursuing the course of their choice. Students are allowed to work both on campus and off campus for up to 20 hours during the week when the academic session is in progress and full time during vacations.[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Scholarships for Study in Australia\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]There are many scholarship programs which students can pursue who are planning to study in Australia but are not able to afford the fees. The scholarships typically cover either the entire or part of the costs of tuition in Australia. Here are some of the most coveted<strong><a href=\"https://www.studyinaustralia.gov.au/english/australian-education/scholarships\">scholarships for studying in Australia</a></strong>[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=\"0px\" disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"13721\" img_size=\"530*300\" el_class=\"ts-border-radius-1\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][themestek-list icon_type=\"themestek_liviza_business_icon\" icon_icon_themestek_liviza_business_icon=\"themestek-liviza-business-icon themestek-liviza-business-icon-check\" line1=\"R28lMjB0byUyMHRoZSUyMG9mZmljaWFsJTIwd2Vic2l0ZSUyMElFTFRTJTIwYW5kJTIwY3JlYXRlJTIwcHJvZmlsZS4=\" line2=\"Q2hlY2slMjBJbmZvcm1hdGlvbiUyMHByb3ZpZGUlMjBpbiUyMHlvdXIlMjBwYXNzcG9ydC4=\" line3=\"U3BlYWtpbmclMjBvciUyMHdyaXRpbmclMjBzY29yZSUyMHJldmlldyUyMGZvcm0lMjB5b3VyJTIwZXhhbS4=\" line4=\"QWRkaXRpb25hbCUyMHJlcG9ydHMlMjBpbnN0aXR1dGlvbiUyMG9mJTIwY29hY2hpbmclMjBjZW50ZXI=\" line5=\"TmVlZCUyMGV4cGVydGlzZSUyMGhlbHAlMkMlMjB3aGVyZXZlciUyMHlvdSUyMGluJTIwdGhlJTIwd29ybGQu\" css=\".vc_custom_158079253