(13922, 1, '2020-08-05 05:37:54', '2020-08-05 05:37:54', '[vc_row][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Canada Skilled Immigration\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]Canada is the land of immense opportunities. The bountiful maple country is home to multi-cultural individuals from across the world. Canada immigration rules are not as rigorous when compared to other countries, hence is much easier to qualify. The country offers a dynamic range of immigration and visa programs for the employed, self-employed and businessmen categories and for those not qualified under the Immigration programs, the country still offers non-immigrant options such as work permit and student programs and majority of these programs offer permanent resident visa and Immigration. Canada also offers the most supporting social security benefits program for immigrants and their families. Canadas educational and health facilities are among the best in the world and are highly subsidized.\n\nCanada is rated very high when it comes to the best countries to live in the world and is the 7thsafest country to live in with no racial discrimination. It is the third largest country with less population so being a developed country the opportunities are quite high. Moreover, people with the Canadian PR can go and work in USA with a TN visa so Canada is the gateway for USA as well, so while opting for one country you get the opportunity to work in two countries\n\nBeing the Permanent Resident you get all benefits from Government side whether free schooling for your kids , free medical services, Kids allowance, Mothers allowance, Unemployment allowance, Senior Citizen pension( 2 kinds of pensions) even retirement age is 65 years due to healthy lifestyle. It is easy to sponsor your parents and call them on Super Visa or Parental Visa[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Major Skilled Immigration Visa Programs for Canada:\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_tta_accordion active_section=\"0\" collapsible_all=\"true\"][vc_tta_section title=\"Express Entry Program\" tab_id=\"1596605268937-d6c7398e-2997\"][vc_column_text]Immigration to Canada is a famous trend among Skilled workers and Business people these days due this countrys welcoming nature and its benefits. Hence, express entry program in Canada is a popular choice for people who wish to work in Canada. The Express Entry immigration program manage applications for permanent residence under the following Federal Immigration Programs:\n\n1Federal Skilled Worker Program (FSWP),\n2 Federal Skilled Trades Program (FSTP), and\n3Canadian Experience Class (CEC)\n\nMost applicants are evaluated based on their Age, Work Experience, Language ability, Education Skills and other factors.\nPotential candidates will complete an online Express Entry profile and those who meet the criteria of one of the federal immigration programs will be accepted into a pool of candidates. The Express Entry system will be the first step to immigrate to Canada under these programs. There will be no deadline to complete a profile and there will be no caps on the number of candidates that will be accepted to the pool.\n\nAnyone who does not have a job offer supported by a Labor Market Impact Assessment (LMIA), or a nomination from a province or territory, must register with Employment and Social Development Canadas (ESDC) Job Bank. Job Bank will help connect Express Entry candidates with eligible employers in Canada.\n\nProvinces and territories will also be able to recruit candidates from the Express Entry system through their Provincial Nominee Programs to meet local labor market needs.\n\nCandidates with the highest scores in the pool will receive Invitation to Apply.\n\nAdditional Points incurred if in case candidate has\n\n1. A job offer supported by a Labor Market Impact Assessment, or\n2. A nomination by a province or territory\n\nThese additional points will ensure that candidates rank is high enough to be invited to apply at the next eligible draw of candidates.\nCitizenship and Immigration Canada will process the majority of complete applications with all the necessary supporting documents in six months or less.\nCandidates stay in the pool up to 12 months. If they do not get an Invitation to Apply for permanent residence within 12 months of submitting an Express Entry profile, they can resubmit a new profile only if they are eligible again.\n\nCandidates with Invitation to apply have 60 days to submit a complete Application for Permanent Residence.\n<ol>\n 	<li><strong>FEDERAL SKILLED WORKERS</strong>\nThe Federal Skilled Workers class is the single largest category. Applicants are selected based on age, education, occupation, work experience, English or French ability, and close relatives in Canada. The objective is to achieve the pass-mark i.e. 67 out of 100.</li>\n</ol>\nEligibility Criteria:\n\nIn order to qualify for Canada Immigration Visa for permanent residency as a Canadian Federal Skilled Worker applicant, one must:\n<ul>\n 	<li>have a minimum of one year if uninterrupted full time (or equivalent) work experience in the past 10 years under a skilled occupations (Skill Type O,A, B) or</li>\n 	<li>have an arranged employment (job offered by a Canadian employer) with regard to the Labour Market Impact Assessment criteria</li>\n 	<li>have completed two years of study in Canada towards a PhD or a PhD in Canada, from a recognized Canadian institution, and</li>\n 	<li>pass the language ability exam for one of Canadas two official languages  English and French</li>\n</ul>\nSelection Factor:\n\nThe Canadian Federal Skilled Worker Program is points based, with applicants being assessed on criteria such as age, education, experience, language skills, adaptability, and whether they have an existing job offer in Canada.\n<ol start=\"2\">\n 	<li><strong>Federal Skilled Trades Program</strong></li>\n</ol>\nThe Federal Skilled Trades Program is for people who want to become permanent residents based on being qualified in a skilled trade.\n\nEligibility Criteria:\n\nTo be eligible for a Canada Immigration (Permanent Resident) Visa, Federal Skilled Trades applicants must fulfill the following criteria:-\n<ul>\n 	<li>They must have offers of employment from up to two employers in Canada for a minimum period of one year, or Certificate of Qualification from a territory or province of Canada</li>\n 	<li>They must furnish a proof of basic language proficiency of any one of the two official languages of Canada  English or French</li>\n 	<li>They must have obtained two years of qualified work experience in the skilled trade in the last five years</li>\n 	<li>They must be able to demonstrate their skills and experience, and that they have performed all the essential duties of their respective occupation</li>\n 	<li>have an offer of full-time employment for a total period of at least one year or a certificate of qualification in that skilled trade issued by a Canadian provincial or territorial authority.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>3Canadian Experience Class (CEC)</strong>\n\nUnder this category, Candidate must complete an Express Entry profile as the first step to immigrate to Canada permanently. The Canadian Experience Class (CEC) is an immigration category that intends to help Canadas temporary foreign workers and international graduates in obtaining a Permanent Resident status. The CEC is a popular immigration path for individuals who are already living and working in Canada.\n\nEligibility Criteria:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Candidate must have at least 12 months of skilled work experience in Canada, in the last three years (before they apply).</li>\n 	<li>Work experience should be full-time OR an equal amount in part-time</li>\n 	<li>gained your work experience in Canada with the proper authorization</li>\n 	<li>meet the required language levels in writing, reading , listening &amp; speaking</li>\n 	<li>planned to live outside the province of Quebec</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Quebec Skilled Program\" tab_id=\"1596605268968-09d8d3ff-7b19\"][vc_column_text]Quebec having the special agreement with the Government of Canada on immigration has its own rules for choosing immigrants who will adapt well to living there. The Quebec Skilled Program is aimed at people who wish to work in Quebec. In order to immigrate to Quebec, applicants must obtain a certificate of selection from the Quebec province before applying for the permanent residence application to Canada.\n\nThe process of applying immigration under the Quebec Skilled Worker program consists of the following steps:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Submission of an Expression of Interest tosettle in Quebecand entry intoQuebecs Expression of Interest Bank.</li>\n 	<li>Successful selection from theQuebec Expression of Interest Bankresults in aninvitation to applyfor the QSWP.</li>\n 	<li>Submission of an application for a Quebec Selection Certificate, or certificat de slection du Qubec (CSQ) to the MIDI.</li>\n 	<li>Submission of a Canadian permanent residence application to the Federal Government.</li>\n</ol>\nAfter submitting an Expression of Interest to MIDI, candidates will be entered into the Quebec Expression of Interest Bank.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Provincial Nominees\" tab_id=\"1596605416328-8ff57181-a7ea\"][vc_column_text]Most provinces and territories in Canada can nominate immigrants with skills, education and work experience to contribute to the economy of that province or territory &amp; who must want to live there.\n\nEach province and territory has its own streams (immigration programs that target certain groups) and criteria for their PNP. Provinces and territories may target students, business people, skilled workers or semi-skilled workers. The province of Quebec does not have a PNP. To apply for the Provincial Nominee Programs, the applicant must apply to a province or territory for a nomination or must be nominated by that province or territory.\n\nUnder the Provincial Nominee Program (PNP), an employer has the liberty to nominate a limited number of candidates for certain skilled positions and further make an application to a participating state for sponsorship of the work permit for Canada.\n\nAt present, PNP exists in the following territories and provinces of Canada:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Alberta</li>\n 	<li>British Columbia</li>\n 	<li>Manitoba</li>\n 	<li>New Brunswick</li>\n 	<li>Newfoundland and Labrador</li>\n 	<li>Northwest Territories</li>\n 	<li>Nova Scotia</li>\n 	<li>Ontario</li>\n 	<li>Prince Edward Island</li>\n 	<li>Saskatchewan</li>\n 	<li>Yukon</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=\"0px\" disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"13721\" img_size=\"530*300\" el_class=\"ts-border-radius-1\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][themestek-list icon_type=\"themestek_liviza_business_icon\" icon_icon_themestek_liviza_business_icon=\"themestek-liviza-business-icon themestek-liviza-business-icon-check\" line1=\"R28lMjB0byUyMHRoZSUyMG9mZmljaWFsJTIwd2Vic2l0ZSUyMElFTFRTJTIwYW5kJTIwY3JlYXRlJTIwcHJvZmlsZS4=\" line2=\"Q2hlY2slMjBJbmZvcm1hdGlvbiUyMHByb3ZpZGUlMjBpbiUyMHlvdXIlMjBwYXNzcG9ydC4=\" line3=\"U3BlYWtpbmclMjBvciUyMHdyaXRpbmclMjBzY29yZSUyMHJldmlldyUyMGZvcm0lMjB5b3VyJTIwZXhhbS4=\" line4=\"QWRkaXRpb25hbCUyMHJlcG9ydHMlMjBpbnN0aXR1dGlvbiUyMG9mJTIwY29hY2hpbmclMjBjZW50ZXI=\" line5=\"TmVlZCUyMGV4cGVydGlzZSUyMGhlbHAlMkMlMjB3aGVyZXZlciUyMHlvdSUyMGluJTIwdGhlJTIwd29ybGQu\" css=\".vc_custom_1580792535630{padding-bottom: 20px !important;}\" el_class=\"themestek-list-sep\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"How to Prepare for IELTS Exam\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_single_image image=\"13754\" img_size=\"ful