(13931, 1, '2020-08-05 05:49:42', '2020-08-05 05:49:42', '[vc_row][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Australia Skilled Immigration\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]Australia -an island continent is worlds sixth largest country (7,682,300 sq. km). With the 10th highest nominal per capital income worldwide and low unemployment rate (around 5%) Australiaprovides newer opportunities to job seekers. Australia also ranks high in terms of government transparency, civil liberties, quality of life, economic freedom, and education.\n\nThe Australian dollar exchange rate is on the higher side compared to other economies and the pay scale is on higher side even in the part time jobs. Australias healthcare system is among the best ones in the world and the continent offers un-spoilt nature (over 500 national parks)and the cleanest air to breath in.Skilled migrants wishing to work in Australia on a permanent basis areassessed on apoints based system; with points awarded for work experience, qualifications and language proficiency. Other ways of obtaining immigration visas to Australia include theAustralian Family Migration, and Humanitarian Programs. One get all benefits of Kids free Education allowance, Medical allowance, Pension and so on while being the Permanent resident.[/vc_column_text][themestek-custom-heading text=\"Major Skilled Immigration Visa Programs for Australia\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_column_text]Through this Australian immigration program, applicants can obtain a permanent Australian visa. However, they must have the necessary work experience, qualifications, and language proficiency to meet the Australian immigration requirements. The following are the major categories for skilled immigration in Australia:[/vc_column_text][vc_tta_accordion active_section=\"0\" collapsible_all=\"true\"][vc_tta_section title=\"Skilled  Independent (Subclass 189)\" tab_id=\"1596605268937-d6c7398e-2997be14-84bc\"][vc_column_text]This visa offers the candidate a permanent residency in Australia with their family and falls under the Australian Immigration points-based system. Applicants must furnish that they possess the qualification or the skills of an occupation in the Skilled Occupation List (SOL). Skilled Independent Visa (Subclass 189) applicants are required to obtain a minimum of 65 points on a point assessment.\n\nEligibility:\n\nThe applicants have to satisfy the basic requirements to migrate under the skilled sponsored visa and must meet the 65 points to file for a visa.\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Age:</strong>Under 45 years of age at time of invitation.\n<strong>English language:</strong>The applicant should prove that he/she meets the English language of competent level by submitting the test results before the application is submitted.</li>\n 	<li><strong>Nominated Occupations:</strong>The applicant should nominate an occupation on the Medium and Long term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL) that matches with his/her skills, qualifications and work experience.\n<strong>Skill Assessment:</strong>It is mandatory for an applicant to get a positive skill assessment for a nominated occupation before the visa application is submitted.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong><u>Benefits of Visa:</u></strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>stay in Australia indefinitely</li>\n 	<li>work and study in Australia</li>\n 	<li>enroll in Medicare, Australias scheme for health-related care and expenses</li>\n 	<li>sponsor eligible relatives for permanent residence</li>\n 	<li>travel to and from Australia for five years</li>\n 	<li>Apply for Australian citizenship, if eligible</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Skilled  Nominated (Sub Class 190)\" tab_id=\"1596605268968-09d8d3ff-7b19be14-84bc\"][vc_column_text]This points-based Permanent Resident visa is for skilled workers who are nominated by an Australian state or territory and is an option to the individuals who cannot meet the Skilled Independent criteria and for those applicants whose occupation is not listed in the Medium and Long term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL). The basic requirement of this visa is to get sponsorship from a sponsoring State/ Territory in Australia. Applicants should also meet the points test by scoring 65.\n\nEligibility:\n\nThe applicants have to satisfy the basic requirements to migrate under the skilled sponsored visa and must meet the 65 points to file for a visa.\n<ul>\n 	<li><strong>Age:</strong>Under 45 years of age at time of invitation.\n<strong>English language:</strong>The applicant should prove that he/she meets the English language of competent level by submitting the test results before the application is submitted.\n<strong>Nominated Occupations:</strong>The applicant should nominate an occupation in the Medium and Long term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL) or Short term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) that is relevant to the applicants skills, qualifications and recent work experience and the occupation should also be available in the respective state that will sponsor the state nomination.\n<strong>Skill Assessment:</strong>It is mandatory for an applicant to get a positive skill assessment for a nominated occupation before the application is lodged.\n<strong>Maintenance funds:</strong>The applicants should show sufficient maintenance funds to obtain sponsorship from state territory.\n<strong>Health &amp; character requirements:</strong>The applicant has to meet with health and character requirements.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Benefits of Visa:</strong>\n<ul>\n 	<li>stay in Australia indefinitely</li>\n 	<li>work and study in Australia</li>\n 	<li>enroll in Medicare, Australias scheme for health-related care and expenses</li>\n 	<li>sponsor eligible relatives for permanent residence</li>\n 	<li>travel to and from Australia for five years</li>\n 	<li>Apply for Australian citizenship, if eligible</li>\n</ul>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Skilled  Regional Sponsored (Provisional) (Subclass 489)\" tab_id=\"1596605416328-8ff57181-a7eabe14-84bc\"][vc_column_text]The Skilled Regional (Provisional) Subclass 489 visa is a provisional visa which requires holders to live and work in a regional area to obtain permanent residence. To qualify, candidate must be sponsored by either a relative living in a designated area or a State or Territory Government.\n\nEligibility:\n\nThe applicants have to satisfy the basic requirements to migrate under the Skilled Regional State or Relative Sponsored Visa and must secure 65 points to file the Visa.\n\n<strong>Age:</strong>Under 45 years.\n<strong>English language:</strong>The applicant should prove that he/she meets the English language of competence level by submitting the test results before the application is submitted.\n<strong>Nominated Occupation:</strong>The applicant should nominate an occupation on the Short term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) or Medium and Long term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL). If the he/ she wish to live in the designated area, the applicant should apply for relative sponsored Visa.\n<strong>Skill Assessment:</strong>It is mandatory for an applicant to get a positive skill assessment for a nominated occupation before the application is filed.\n<strong>Maintenance funds:</strong>The applicants should show sufficient maintenance funds to obtain sponsorship from state territory if applying for state /territory nominated regional visa.\n<strong>Health &amp; character requirements:</strong>The applicant has to meet all the health and character requirements.\n\n<strong>Sponsorship by a Relative living in a Designated Area</strong>\nThe applicant can apply for a Subclass 489 visa if he/she is sponsored by a relative living in a Designated Area. The relative must be an Australian citizen, permanent resident or Eligible New Zealand Citizen. The following relatives can sponsor for the Subclass 489 visa:\nParents, Grandparents\nBrothers and Sisters\nUncles and Aunts\nNephews and Nieces, First Cousins[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_accordion][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=\"0px\" disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"13721\" img_size=\"530*300\" el_class=\"ts-border-radius-1\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][themestek-list icon_type=\"themestek_liviza_business_icon\" icon_icon_themestek_liviza_business_icon=\"themestek-liviza-business-icon themestek-liviza-business-icon-check\" line1=\"R28lMjB0byUyMHRoZSUyMG9mZmljaWFsJTIwd2Vic2l0ZSUyMElFTFRTJTIwYW5kJTIwY3JlYXRlJTIwcHJvZmlsZS4=\" line2=\"Q2hlY2slMjBJbmZvcm1hdGlvbiUyMHByb3ZpZGUlMjBpbiUyMHlvdXIlMjBwYXNzcG9ydC4=\" line3=\"U3BlYWtpbmclMjBvciUyMHdyaXRpbmclMjBzY29yZSUyMHJldmlldyUyMGZvcm0lMjB5b3VyJTIwZXhhbS4=\" line4=\"QWRkaXRpb25hbCUyMHJlcG9ydHMlMjBpbnN0aXR1dGlvbiUyMG9mJTIwY29hY2hpbmclMjBjZW50ZXI=\" line5=\"TmVlZCUyMGV4cGVydGlzZSUyMGhlbHAlMkMlMjB3aGVyZXZlciUyMHlvdSUyMGluJTIwdGhlJTIwd29ybGQu\" css=\".vc_custom_1580792535630{padding-bottom: 20px !important;}\" el_class=\"themestek-list-sep\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row disable_element=\"yes\"][vc_column][themestek-custom-heading text=\"How to Prepare for IELTS Exam\" font_container=\"tag:h4|text_align:left\"][vc_single_image image=\"13754\" img_size=\"full\" el_class=\"ts-border-radius-1\" css=\".vc_custom_1582005531976{padding-top: 10px !important;}\"][vc_row_inner gap=\"0px\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Listening\" font_container=\"tag:h6|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Roboto%3A100%2C100italic%2C300%2C300italic%2Cregular%2Citalic%2C500%2C500italic%2C700%2C700italic%2C900%2C900italic|font_style:500%20bold%20regular%3A500%3Anormal\"][vc_column_text]Many desktop publishing packages and web page editors now use Lorem Ipsum as their default model text, and a search for alphabet infancy.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_custom_headi